body: "## Context\nFiled by the 2026-07-03 concurrency audit: under parallel multi-agent mutation stress, contended item locks fail immediately with lock_conflict, forcing every agent to implement its own retry loop (or lose work). Data integrity held in all stress runs; the gap is ergonomics/self-healing, not corruption.\n\n## Design (implemented, uncommitted as of 2026-07-04)\n- `acquireLock` gains a bounded wait loop: exponential backoff 25ms → 200ms with full jitter (0.5x–1.5x), waiting up to a budget before surfacing lock_conflict.\n- Budget resolution order: `PM_LOCK_WAIT_MS` env (non-negative int) > `locks.wait_ms` from settings > 0 (fail-fast = exact pre-feature behavior). Default shipped in SETTINGS_DEFAULTS: 3000ms. Config key `locks_wait_ms` (nested-settings descriptor, `pm config set locks_wait_ms <n>`), optional in the settings validator so existing settings.json files stay valid.\n- Stale-lock handling folded into the same loop: stale locks are removed (subject to force_required_for_stale_lock governance) with removals capped at MAX_STALE_LOCK_REMOVALS=3 to prevent livelock between competing waiters.\n- On exhausted budget, lock_conflict error now carries `recovery.retry_after_ms: 250` (new optional field on PmCliErrorRecoveryPayload) so agents/MCP clients can machine-read when to retry; message appends \"after waiting <n>ms\".\n- `waitMs` threaded through acquireLock call sites including restore and history-rewrite.\n\n## Constraints / decisions\n- 0 must remain a valid budget meaning fail-fast (backward compat + tests that assert immediate conflict).\n- Jittered sleep uses Math.random by design (production code path; the no-Date/no-random rule applies to workflow scripts, not src).\n- Interacts with pm-zwib (stale-lock takeover race): the removal cap bounds the blast radius but does NOT fix the two-waiters-both-remove race — pm-zwib stays open and depends on this item.\n\n## Remaining before close (per AC)\n- CONFIGURATION.md docs for locks_wait_ms / PM_LOCK_WAIT_MS.\n- contracts:update if any flag surface changed.\n- Parallel-mutation stress evidence recorded via pm test."
